use gnome-session-properties to add/remove gnome apps at startup
see '/usr/share/gnome-session/sessions/i3-gnome.session' to disable:
* gnome-settings-daemon (gnome=keyring, ...)
* gnome-panel
* notification-daemon

In '~/.config/i3/config':
* use 'exec gnome-session-quit'			:logout
* use 'exec gnome-session-quit --poweroff'	:shutdown menu
* use 'exec gnome-screensaver-command -l 	:locks screen (probly requires i3lock)

In '~/.xprofile':
* add TERMINAL='gnome-terminal'			:gnome-term/etc as default